\date{2025-01-08}
\title{Disjoint Set}
\taxon{definitions}

\p{
  Disjoint set（并查集） is a data structure that keeps track of equivalence classes of all elements in a set.

  It supports two operations:

  \ul{
    \li{\code{find(x)}: return the representative of the set that element #{x} belongs to.}
    \li{\code{union(x, y)}: merge the sets that contain #{x} and #{y}.}
  }
}
